The Telegraph - Calcutta : International

 Saturday, November 19, 2005 

 Wine violence

 Lyon (France), Nov. 18 (Reuters): Festivities marking the arrival of this years Beaujolais Nouveau turned violent in the southeastern French city of Grenoble today, when more than 30 people were injured in clashes between students and police.

 Todays violence broke out after more than 2,000 people, mostly students, left bars where they had been celebrating the arrival of the popular French wine. The wine traditionally goes on sale on the third Thursday of November.

 Youths attacked firemen called out to attend to an injured person and began to throw missiles at police who arrived to back up the firemen. Wine bottles were thrown from apartment windows. 




